      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\RandD\\python_oci_backend_architecture.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Python Backend Architecture for Oracle OCI Always Free\n2: \n3: **Document Version:** 1.0\n4: **Date:** 2026-03-06\n5: **Classification:** Internal R&D\n6: **Purpose:** Architecture for Python-based managed pedagogical service on Oracle OCI\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Reading Priority (MoSCoW)\n11: \n12: | Section | Priority | Time |\n13: |---------|----------|------|\n14: | **Why Python** | MUST | 3 min |\n15: | **OCI Always Free Specs** | MUST | 3 min |\n16: | **Architecture Overview** | MUST | 5 min |\n17: | **FastAPI Service Design** | SHOULD | 10 min |\n18: | **Deployment Strategy** | SHOULD | 5 min |\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## Why Python Over JavaScript for Backend\n23: \n24: | Factor | JavaScript/Node.js | Python | Winner |\n25: |--------|-------------------|--------|--------|\n26: | **AI/ML libraries** | Wrappers around Python | Native (PyTorch, ONNX, HuggingFace) | Python |\n27: | **Edge inference** | ONNX.js (limited) | ONNX Runtime (full) | Python |\n28: | **Async performance** | Good (event loop) | Great (asyncio + uvloop) | Tie |\n29: | **OCI SDK** | Community maintained | Oracle official SDK | Python |\n30: | **Cold start** | Faster | Slower (mitigated by uvicorn) | Node |\n31: | **Type safety** | TypeScript | Pydantic + type hints | Tie |\n32: | **ARM performance** | Good | Excellent (numpy, scipy optimised) | Python |\n33: | **Memory efficiency** | Higher baseline | Lower with proper setup | Python |\n34: \n35: **Verdict:** Python wins for AI-heavy backend on ARM (OCI Always Free).\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## Oracle OCI Always Free Specifications\n40: \n41: ### Compute Resources (Free Forever)\n42: \n43: | Resource | Specification | Notes |\n44: |----------|--------------|-------|\n45: | **ARM Ampere A1** | 4 OCPUs, 24 GB RAM | Split across up to 4 VMs |\n46: | **AMD EPYC** | 2 VMs, 1/8 OCPU each, 1 GB RAM | x86 fallback |\n47: | **Boot volume** | 200 GB total | Across all instances |\n48: | **Outbound data** | 10 TB/month | Generous for API traffic |\n49: \n50: ### Recommended Split for SDTP\n51: \n52: | Instance | OCPUs | RAM | Purpose |\n53: |----------|-------|-----|---------|\n54: | **sdtp-api** | 2 | 12 GB | FastAPI + inference |\n55: | **sdtp-db** | 1 | 6 GB | PostgreSQL |\n56: | **sdtp-cache** | 1 | 6 GB | Redis + model cache |\n57: \n58: ### Additional Free Services\n59: \n60: | Service | Free Tier | Use Case |\n61: |---------|-----------|----------|\n62: | **Autonomous DB** | 20 GB, 1 OCPU | Ledger storage, analytics |\n63: | **Object Storage** | 10 GB | Model weights, artifacts |\n64: | **Load Balancer** | 1 flexible | HTTPS termination |\n65: | **DNS** | Unlimited queries | sdtp.forge-protocol |\n66: | **Vault** | 20 keys | API key management |\n67: | **Logging** | 10 GB/month | Observability |\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ## Architecture Overview\n72: \n73: ```\n74: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n75: │  ORACLE OCI ALWAYS FREE DEPLOYMENT                             │\n76: │  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────  │\n77: │                                                                  │\n78: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n79: │  │  EDGE / CDN (Cloudflare - Optional)                      │  │\n80: │  │  └── Static assets, DDoS protection                      │  │\n81: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n82: │                              │                                   │\n83: │                              ▼                                   │\n84: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n85: │  │  OCI LOAD BALANCER (Free Tier)                           │  │\n86: │  │  └── HTTPS termination, routing                          │  │\n87: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n88: │                              │                                   │\n89: │         ┌────────────────────┼────────────────────┐             │\n90: │         ▼                    ▼                    ▼             │\n91: │  ┌────────────┐      ┌────────────┐      ┌────────────┐        │\n92: │  │ sdtp-api   │      │ sdtp-db    │      │ sdtp-cache │        │\n93: │  │ (ARM A1)   │      │ (ARM A1)   │      │ (ARM A1)   │        │\n94: │  │ 2 OCPU     │      │ 1 OCPU     │      │ 1 OCPU     │        │\n95: │  │ 12 GB RAM  │      │ 6 GB RAM   │      │ 6 GB RAM   │        │\n96: │  │            │      │            │      │            │        │\n97: │  │ FastAPI    │◄────►│ PostgreSQL │◄────►│ Redis      │        │\n98: │  │ Uvicorn    │      │ 16         │      │ 7.x        │        │\n99: │  │ ONNX RT    │      │            │      │ Model LRU  │        │\n100: │  └────────────┘      └────────────┘      └────────────┘        │\n101: │         │                                                        │\n102: │         ▼                                                        │\n103: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n104: │  │  OCI OBJECT STORAGE (10 GB Free)                         │  │\n105: │  │  └── ONNX models, .forge templates, evidence exports     │  │\n106: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n107: │                                                                  │\n108: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n109: ```\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## FastAPI Service Design\n114: \n115: ### Project Structure\n116: \n117: ```\n118: sdtp-api/\n119: ├── app/\n120: │   ├── __init__.py\n121: │   ├── main.py                 # FastAPI app entry\n122: │   ├── config.py               # Pydantic settings\n123: │   │\n124: │   ├── api/\n125: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n126: │   │   ├── v1/\n127: │   │   │   ├── __init__.py\n128: │   │   │   ├── forge.py        # .forge validation endpoints\n129: │   │   │   ├── inference.py    # AI inference endpoints\n130: │   │   │   ├── finops.py       # Budget tracking endpoints\n131: │   │   │   ├── evidence.py     # Evidence capture endpoints\n132: │   │   │   └── health.py       # Health checks\n133: │   │   └── router.py           # API router aggregation\n134: │   │\n135: │   ├── core/\n136: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n137: │   │   ├── security.py         # API key validation\n138: │   │   ├── rate_limit.py       # Rate limiting\n139: │   │   └── middleware.py       # CORS, logging, etc.\n140: │   │\n141: │   ├── services/\n142: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n143: │   │   ├── forge_parser.py     # .forge file parsing\n144: │   │   ├── inference.py        # ONNX inference service\n145: │   │   ├── finops_ledger.py    # Cost tracking\n146: │   │   └── evidence.py         # Evidence generation\n147: │   │\n148: │   ├── models/\n149: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n150: │   │   ├── forge.py            # Pydantic models for .forge\n151: │   │   ├── inference.py        # Request/response models\n152: │   │   └── finops.py           # FinOps models\n153: │   │\n154: │   └── db/\n155: │       ├── __init__.py\n156: │       ├── session.py          # SQLAlchemy async session\n157: │       └── models.py           # ORM models\n158: │\n159: ├── tests/\n160: │   └── ...\n161: │\n162: ├── models/                     # ONNX model weights\n163: │   └── phi-3-mini-q4.onnx\n164: │\n165: ├── pyproject.toml\n166: ├── Dockerfile\n167: └── docker-compose.yml\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ### Core Application (main.py)\n171: \n172: ```python\n173: from fastapi import FastAPI\n174: from fastapi.middleware.cors import CORSMiddleware\n175: from contextlib import asynccontextmanager\n176: \n177: from app.api.router import api_router\n178: from app.core.middleware import LoggingMiddleware, FinOpsMiddleware\n179: from app.services.inference import InferenceService\n180: from app.config import settings\n181: \n182: \n183: @asynccontextmanager\n184: async def lifespan(app: FastAPI):\n185:     # Startup: load ONNX models into memory\n186:     app.state.inference = InferenceService()\n187:     await app.state.inference.load_models()\n188:     yield\n189:     # Shutdown: cleanup\n190:     await app.state.inference.unload_models()\n191: \n192: \n193: app = FastAPI(\n194:     title=\"SDTP API\",\n195:     description=\"Software-Defined Training Protocol managed service\",\n196:     version=\"1.0.0\",\n197:     lifespan=lifespan,\n198: )\n199: \n200: # Middleware\n201: app.add_middleware(\n202:     CORSMiddleware,\n203:     allow_origins=settings.cors_origins,\n204:     allow_credentials=True,\n205:     allow_methods=[\"*\"],\n206:     allow_headers=[\"*\"],\n207: )\n208: app.add_middleware(LoggingMiddleware)\n209: app.add_middleware(FinOpsMiddleware)\n210: \n211: # Routes\n212: app.include_router(api_router, prefix=\"/api/v1\")\n213: \n214: \n215: @app.get(\"/health\")\n216: async def health():\n217:     return {\"status\": \"healthy\", \"version\": \"1.0.0\"}\n218: ```\n219: \n220: ### Inference Service (services/inference.py)\n221: \n222: ```python\n223: import onnxruntime as ort\n224: from pathlib import Path\n225: from typing import Optional\n226: import numpy as np\n227: \n228: from app.config import settings\n229: from app.models.inference import InferenceRequest, InferenceResponse\n230: from app.services.finops_ledger import FinOpsLedger\n231: \n232: \n233: class InferenceService:\n234:     def __init__(self):\n235:         self.sessions: dict[str, ort.InferenceSession] = {}\n236:         self.ledger = FinOpsLedger()\n237: \n238:     async def load_models(self):\n239:         \"\"\"Load ONNX models at startup.\"\"\"\n240:         model_dir = Path(settings.model_dir)\n241: \n242:         # Use ARM-optimised execution providers\n243:         providers = ['CPUExecutionProvider']\n244:         if settings.use_arm_optimisation:\n245:             # ARM NEON optimisations\n246:             sess_options = ort.SessionOptions()\n247:             sess_options.intra_op_num_threads = settings.inference_threads\n248:             sess_options.graph_optimization_level = ort.GraphOptimizationLevel.ORT_ENABLE_ALL\n249: \n250:         for model_path in model_dir.glob(\"*.onnx\"):\n251:             model_name = model_path.stem\n252:             self.sessions[model_name] = ort.InferenceSession(\n253:                 str(model_path),\n254:                 sess_options=sess_options,\n255:                 providers=providers,\n256:             )\n257: \n258:     async def infer(\n259:         self,\n260:         request: InferenceRequest,\n261:         session_id: str,\n262:         budget_remaining: float,\n263:     ) -> InferenceResponse:\n264:         \"\"\"Run inference with FinOps tracking.\"\"\"\n265: \n266:         # Pre-flight budget check\n267:         estimated_cost = self._estimate_cost(request)\n268:         if estimated_cost > budget_remaining:\n269:             return InferenceResponse(\n270:                 success=False,\n271:                 error=\"budget_exhausted\",\n272:                 cost=0.0,\n273:             )\n274: \n275:         # Run inference\n276:         session = self.sessions.get(request.model, self.sessions[\"phi-3-mini-q4\"])\n277: \n278:         # Tokenize and run\n279:         inputs = self._prepare_inputs(request.prompt)\n280:         outputs = session.run(None, inputs)\n281: \n282:         # Decode response\n283:         response_text = self._decode_outputs(outputs)\n284: \n285:         # Calculate actual cost\n286:         tokens_in = len(request.prompt.split())  # Simplified\n287:         tokens_out = len(response_text.split())\n288:         actual_cost = self._calculate_cost(tokens_in, tokens_out, request.model)\n289: \n290:         # Log to ledger\n291:         await self.ledger.log(\n292:             session_id=session_id,\n293:             model=request.model,\n294:             tokens_in=tokens_in,\n295:             tokens_out=tokens_out,\n296:             cost=actual_cost,\n297:         )\n298: \n299:         return InferenceResponse(\n300:             success=True,\n301:             text=response_text,\n302:             tokens_in=tokens_in,\n303:             tokens_out=tokens_out,\n304:             cost=actual_cost,\n305:         )\n306: \n307:     def _estimate_cost(self, request: InferenceRequest) -> float:\n308:         \"\"\"Estimate cost before running inference.\"\"\"\n309:         # Local inference is free\n310:         return 0.0\n311: \n312:     def _calculate_cost(self, tokens_in: int, tokens_out: int, model: str) -> float:\n313:         \"\"\"Calculate actual cost (local = free).\"\"\"\n314:         # Local ONNX inference has no per-token cost\n315:         # Track for carbon accounting only\n316:         return 0.0\n317: ```\n318: \n319: ### FinOps Ledger (services/finops_ledger.py)\n320: \n321: ```python\n322: from datetime import datetime\n323: from typing import Optional\n324: import json\n325: from pathlib import Path\n326: \n327: from sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import AsyncSession\n328: from app.db.session import get_session\n329: from app.db.models import InferenceLog\n330: \n331: \n332: class FinOpsLedger:\n333:     \"\"\"Append-only ledger for inference cost tracking.\"\"\"\n334: \n335:     async def log(\n336:         self,\n337:         session_id: str,\n338:         model: str,\n339:         tokens_in: int,\n340:         tokens_out: int,\n341:         cost: float,\n342:         provider: str = \"local-onnx\",\n343:     ):\n344:         \"\"\"Log an inference call.\"\"\"\n345:         entry = InferenceLog(\n346:             timestamp=datetime.utcnow(),\n347:             session_id=session_id,\n348:             provider=provider,\n349:             model=model,\n350:             tokens_in=tokens_in,\n351:             tokens_out=tokens_out,\n352:             cost_gbp=cost,\n353:         )\n354: \n355:         async with get_session() as session:\n356:             session.add(entry)\n357:             await session.commit()\n358: \n359:     async def get_session_spend(self, session_id: str) -> float:\n360:         \"\"\"Get total spend for a session.\"\"\"\n361:         async with get_session() as session:\n362:             result = await session.execute(\n363:                 \"SELECT SUM(cost_gbp) FROM inference_logs WHERE session_id = :sid\",\n364:                 {\"sid\": session_id}\n365:             )\n366:             return result.scalar() or 0.0\n367: \n368:     async def get_session_budget_remaining(\n369:         self,\n370:         session_id: str,\n371:         max_budget: float,\n372:     ) -> float:\n373:         \"\"\"Get remaining budget for a session.\"\"\"\n374:         spent = await self.get_session_spend(session_id)\n375:         return max(0.0, max_budget - spent)\n376: ```\n377: \n378: ### .forge Validation Endpoint (api/v1/forge.py)\n379: \n380: ```python\n381: from fastapi import APIRouter, HTTPException\n382: from pydantic import ValidationError\n383: \n384: from app.models.forge import ForgeFile, ForgeValidationResponse\n385: from app.services.forge_parser import ForgeParser\n386: \n387: router = APIRouter(prefix=\"/forge\", tags=[\"forge\"])\n388: \n389: \n390: @router.post(\"/validate\", response_model=ForgeValidationResponse)\n391: async def validate_forge_file(content: str):\n392:     \"\"\"Validate a .forge file against the SDTP specification.\"\"\"\n393:     try:\n394:         parser = ForgeParser()\n395:         forge_file = parser.parse(content)\n396: \n397:         return ForgeValidationResponse(\n398:             valid=True,\n399:             forge_file=forge_file,\n400:             errors=[],\n401:         )\n402:     except ValidationError as e:\n403:         return ForgeValidationResponse(\n404:             valid=False,\n405:             forge_file=None,\n406:             errors=[err[\"msg\"] for err in e.errors()],\n407:         )\n408: \n409: \n410: @router.post(\"/generate\")\n411: async def generate_from_intent(intent: str, scaffold: str = \"guided\"):\n412:     \"\"\"Generate a .forge file from natural language intent.\"\"\"\n413:     # Use local inference to generate\n414:     # ... implementation\n415:     pass\n416: ```\n417: \n418: ---\n419: \n420: ## Deployment Strategy\n421: \n422: ### Docker Compose for Local Development\n423: \n424: ```yaml\n425: version: '3.8'\n426: \n427: services:\n428:   api:\n429:     build: .\n430:     ports:\n431:      - \"8000:8000\"\n432:     environment:\n433:      - DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://sdtp:sdtp@db:5432/sdtp\n434:      - REDIS_URL=redis://cache:6379\n435:      - MODEL_DIR=/models\n436:     volumes:\n437:      - ./models:/models:ro\n438:     depends_on:\n439:      - db\n440:      - cache\n441: \n442:   db:\n443:     image: postgres:16-alpine\n444:     environment:\n445:      - POSTGRES_USER=sdtp\n446:      - POSTGRES_PASSWORD=sdtp\n447:      - POSTGRES_DB=sdtp\n448:     volumes:\n449:      - pgdata:/var/lib/postgresql/data\n450: \n451:   cache:\n452:     image: redis:7-alpine\n453:     volumes:\n454:      - redisdata:/data\n455: \n456: volumes:\n457:   pgdata:\n458:   redisdata:\n459: ```\n460: \n461: ### Dockerfile (ARM-optimised)\n462: \n463: ```dockerfile\n464: FROM python:3.12-slim\n465: \n466: # Install ARM-optimised dependencies\n467: RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y \\\n468:     build-essential \\\n469:     && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n470: \n471: WORKDIR /app\n472: \n473: # Install Python dependencies\n474: COPY pyproject.toml .\n475: RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -e .\n476: \n477: # Copy application\n478: COPY app/ app/\n479: \n480: # Copy models (or mount as volume)\n481: COPY models/ models/\n482: \n483: # Run with uvicorn\n484: CMD [\"uvicorn\", \"app.main:app\", \"--host\", \"0.0.0.0\", \"--port\", \"8000\", \"--workers\", \"2\"]\n485: ```\n486: \n487: ### OCI Deployment Script\n488: \n489: ```bash\n490: #!/bin/bash\n491: # deploy-oci.sh\n492: \n493: # Variables\n494: COMPARTMENT_ID=\"ocid1.compartment.oc1..your-compartment\"\n495: INSTANCE_NAME=\"sdtp-api\"\n496: SHAPE=\"VM.Standard.A1.Flex\"\n497: OCPUS=2\n498: MEMORY_GB=12\n499: \n500: # Create instance\n501: oci compute instance launch \\\n502:   --compartment-id $COMPARTMENT_ID \\\n503:   --display-name $INSTANCE_NAME \\\n504:   --availability-domain \"AD-1\" \\\n505:   --shape $SHAPE \\\n506:   --shape-config \"{\\\"ocpus\\\": $OCPUS, \\\"memoryInGBs\\\": $MEMORY_GB}\" \\\n507:   --image-id \"ocid1.image.oc1..oracle-linux-9-aarch64\" \\\n508:   --subnet-id $SUBNET_ID \\\n509:   --assign-public-ip true \\\n510:   --ssh-authorized-keys-file ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub\n511: ```\n512: \n513: ---\n514: \n515: ## Performance Considerations\n516: \n517: ### ARM Ampere A1 Optimisations\n518: \n519: | Optimisation | Implementation |\n520: |--------------|----------------|\n521: | **ONNX ARM backend** | Use `CPUExecutionProvider` with NEON |\n522: | **NumPy BLAS** | Install `numpy` with OpenBLAS for ARM |\n523: | **Uvicorn workers** | Match to OCPU count (2) |\n524: | **Model quantisation** | Use INT8/INT4 quantised models |\n525: | **Redis caching** | Cache tokenized inputs |\n526: | **Connection pooling** | SQLAlchemy async pool (20 connections) |\n527: \n528: ### Expected Performance\n529: \n530: | Metric | Estimate |\n531: |--------|----------|\n532: | **Cold start** | ~3s (model loading) |\n533: | **Inference latency (Phi-3 Mini)** | ~500ms per request |\n534: | **Throughput** | ~10-20 req/s (2 OCPU) |\n535: | **Memory usage** | ~4-6 GB (model + app) |\n536: | **Concurrent users** | ~50-100 (with queuing) |\n537: \n538: ---\n539: \n540: ## Migration Path\n541: \n542: ### Phase 1: Keep TypeScript PDE\n543: - Browser PDE stays TypeScript\n544: - Backend API in Python (FastAPI)\n545: - Communication via REST/WebSocket\n546: \n547: ### Phase 2: Python CLI\n548: - Replace Node.js CLI with Python (Click/Typer)\n549: - Faster cold starts\n550: - Shared code with backend\n551: \n552: ### Phase 3: Full Python Backend\n553: - All server-side logic in Python\n554: - TypeScript only for browser\n555: - Monorepo with `pyproject.toml` + `package.json`\n556: \n557: ---\n558: \n559: ## Summary\n560: \n561: | Component | Language | Runtime | Deployment |\n562: |-----------|----------|---------|------------|\n563: | **Browser PDE** | TypeScript | Browser | Static (Cloudflare) |\n564: | **Managed API** | Python | FastAPI + Uvicorn | OCI ARM A1 |\n565: | **Database** | SQL | PostgreSQL 16 | OCI ARM A1 |\n566: | **Cache** | - | Redis 7 | OCI ARM A1 |\n567: | **Models** | ONNX | ONNX Runtime | OCI Object Storage |\n568: | **CLI** | Python | Click/Typer | pip install |\n569: \n570: **Total OCI Always Free cost: £0.00/month**\n571: \n572: ---\n573: \n574: *Document maintained by: R&D Team*\n575: *Last updated: 2026-03-06*\n\n(End of file - total 575 lines)\n</content>",
