      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\.minimax\\sessions\\mvs_655002872be440d685f9c58dcb581f2a\\workspace\\oci_extract\\oracle_uk_free_tier.pdf.txt</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \n2: --- PAGE 1 ---\n3: Here is how Oracle Cloud Free Tier\n4: works\n5: 1\n6: Start with a US$300 cloud credit.*\n7: You’ll have 30 days to use it to test\n8: your applications on all OCI\n9: services, in addition to Always Free\n10: Services in your Free Tier account. 2\n11: At any time during or after the 30-\n12: day period,* switch to a Pay As\n13: You Go account. Pay only for\n14: services that exceed the monthly 3\n15: If you do nothing after 30 days,\n16: you’ll continue to get Always Free\n17: Services in your Free Tier account.\n18: Oracle Cloud Free Tier\n19: Build, test, and deploy applications on Oracle Cloud—for free.\n20: Start for free Sign in to Oracle Cloud\n21: Chatnow\n22: CallSales\n23: +44 207 5626 823\n24: Complete list of local country numbers6/17/26, 5:58 PM Oracle Cloud Free Tier | Oracle United Kingdom\n25: https://www.oracle.com/uk/cloud/free/ 1/8\n26: --- PAGE 2 ---\n27: Oracle Cloud Free Tier\n28: Get cloud credits and start using Oracle Cloud services.\n29: Services available on Oracle Cloud Free Tier\n30: Featured Product \n31: Tier Type \n32: Product Category Filtered by: No Filters applied Clear all\n33: free amounts from Always Free\n34: Services.Sign up now\n35: AI and Machine Learning\n36: Compute\n37: Networking\n38: Oracle Databases\n39: Storage\n40: AI and Machine Learning\n41: Analytics and BI\n42: Compute\n43: Containers and Functions\n44: Developer ServicesSearch\n45: Always Free\n46: TrialTRIAL\n47: AI and Machine Learning\n48: Data Science\n49: Up to 4,700 hours. Build, train,\n50: deploy, and manage machine\n51: learning models. The platform\n52: makes data science collaborative,\n53: scalable, and powerful.\n54: TRIAL\n55: AI and Machine Learning\n56: Oracle Digital Assistant\n57: Up to 51 hours, digital assistants\n58: help accomplish tasks through\n59: natural language conversations,\n60: without having to manage various\n61: apps and web sites.\n62: TRIAL\n63: CallSales\n64: +44 207 5626 823\n65: Complete list of local country numbers6/17/26, 5:58 PM Oracle Cloud Free Tier | Oracle United Kingdom\n66: https://www.oracle.com/uk/cloud/free/ 2/8\n67: --- PAGE 3 ---\n68: Integration\n69: Networking\n70: Observability and Management\n71: Open Source Databases\n72: Oracle Databases\n73: Others\n74: Security\n75: StorageAI and Machine Learning\n76: Language\n77: Tiered pricing based on use\n78: cases. OCI Language is a cloud-\n79: based AI service for performing\n80: sophisticated text analysis at\n81: scale\n82: TRIAL\n83: AI and Machine Learning\n84: Speech\n85: Tiered Pricing based on use\n86: cases. OCI Speech is an AI service\n87: that applies automatic speech\n88: recognition technology to\n89: transform audio-based content to\n90: text\n91: TRIAL\n92: AI and Machine Learning\n93: Vision\n94: Tiered Pricing based on use\n95: cases. OCI Vision is an AI service\n96: for performing deep-learning-\n97: based image analysis at scale.\n98: TRIAL\n99: AI and Machine Learning\n100: Document Understanding\n101: Tierd Pricing. OCI Document\n102: Understanding is an AI service\n103: that enables developers to extract\n104: text, tables, and other key dataCallSales\n105: +44 207 5626 823\n106: Complete list of local country numbers6/17/26, 5:58 PM Oracle Cloud Free Tier | Oracle United Kingdom\n107: https://www.oracle.com/uk/cloud/free/ 3/8\n108: --- PAGE 4 ---\n109: 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8from document files through APIs\n110: and command line interface tools.\n111: TRIAL\n112: Analytics and BI\n113: Analytics Cloud\n114: Up to 4,700 hours. The most\n115: comprehensive analytics in the\n116: cloud.\n117: ALWAYS FREE\n118: Compute\n119: AMD Compute Instance\n120: AMD based Compute VMs with\n121: 1/8 OCPU and 1 GB memory each\n122: Always Free\n123: 2 AMD based compute VMs\n124: ALWAYS FREE\n125: Compute\n126: Arm Compute Instance\n127: Arm-based Ampere A1 cores and\n128: 12 GB of memory usable as 1 VM\n129: or 2 VMs\n130: Always Free\n131: 1,500 OCPU hours and 9,000 GB\n132: hours per month\n133: CallSales\n134: +44 207 5626 823\n135: Complete list of local country numbers6/17/26, 5:58 PM Oracle Cloud Free Tier | Oracle United Kingdom\n136: https://www.oracle.com/uk/cloud/free/ 4/8\n137: --- PAGE 5 ---\n138: Frequently asked questionsClose all\n139: What is Oracle Cloud Free Tier?\n140: Oracle Cloud Free Tier allows you to sign up for an Oracle Cloud account which provides a number of\n141: Always Free services and a Free Trial with US$300 of free credit to use on all eligible Oracle Cloud\n142: Infrastructure services for up to 30 days. The Always Free services are available for an unlimited period\n143: of time. The Free Trial services may be used until your US$300 of free credits are consumed or the 30\n144: days has expired, whichever comes first.\n145: What are Always Free Services?\n146: Always Free services are part of Oracle Cloud Free Tier. Always Free services are available for an\n147: unlimited time. Some limitations apply. As new Always Free services become available, you will\n148: automatically be able to use those as well.\n149: The following services are available as Always Free:\n150: HeatWave\n151: AMD-based Compute\n152: Arm-based Ampere A1 Compute\n153: Block Volume\n154: Object Storage\n155: Archive Storage\n156: Flexible Load Balancer\n157: Flexible Network Load Balancer\n158: Site-to-Site VPN\n159: Autonomous Data Warehouse\n160: Developer Resource\n161: Center Discover, learn, and build.\n162: Create common apps and grow\n163: with generative AI. Enjoy\n164: unmatched capabilities.\n165: Learn moreOracle Architecture\n166: Center Design and implement your\n167: workloads faster and more\n168: efficiently with reference\n169: architectures, quick-start guides,\n170: and other resources.\n171: Learn moreFree training and\n172: accreditation The Oracle Learning Explorer\n173: program offers entry-level training\n174: courses and accreditation for\n175: Oracle's entire product portfolio.\n176: Learn moreHere are some resources to enhance your Oracle\n177: Cloud Free Tier experience\n178: CallSales\n179: +44 207 5626 823\n180: Complete list of local country numbers6/17/26, 5:58 PM Oracle Cloud Free Tier | Oracle United Kingdom\n181: https://www.oracle.com/uk/cloud/free/ 5/8\n182: --- PAGE 6 ---\n183: Autonomous Transaction Processing\n184: Autonomous JSON Database\n185: NoSQL Database (Phoenix Region only)\n186: APEX Application Development\n187: Resource Manager (Terraform)\n188: Monitoring\n189: Notifications\n190: Logging\n191: Application Performance Monitoring\n192: Service Connector Hub\n193: Vault\n194: Bastions\n195: Security Advisor\n196: Virtual Cloud Networks\n197: Site-to-Site VPN\n198: Content Management Starter Edition\n199: Email Delivery\n200: CallSales\n201: +44 207 5626 823\n202: Complete list of local country numbers6/17/26, 5:58 PM Oracle Cloud Free Tier | Oracle United Kingdom\n203: https://www.oracle.com/uk/cloud/free/ 6/8\n204: --- PAGE 7 ---\n205: Is Oracle Cloud Free Tier available in all countries?\n206: Oracle Cloud Free Tier is currently available in all regions where commercial Oracle Cloud Infrastructure\n207: service is available. See the data regions page for detailed service availability. ** If your first-choice data\n208: region isn’t available, please select an adjacent region. If you are unable to find the country or territory\n209: you require, please contact Oracle Sales or Cloud Support using the Chat link in the menu bar. The\n210: Oracle Sales team can help you sign up for Oracle Cloud Free Tier.\n211: Who is eligible for Oracle Cloud Free Tier?\n212: One Oracle Cloud Free Trial or Always Free account is permitted per person. Please note:\n213: Creating or attempting to create multiple free accounts is prohibited.\n214: All contact and billing information provided must be accurate, valid, and used with consent for the\n215: duration of the account.\n216: Accounts left idle for 30 days or more may be deemed abandoned and become eligible for\n217: suspension or termination.\n218: Failure to comply with these requirements or the Cloud Services Agreement (PDF) may result in the\n219: suspension or termination of your account.\n220: Why do I need to provide credit or debit card information when I sign up for Oracle Cloud Free\n221: Tier?\n222: To provide free Oracle Cloud accounts to our valued customers, we need to ensure that you are who\n223: you say you are. We use your contact information and credit/debit card information for account setup\n224: and identity verification. Oracle may periodically check the validity of your card, resulting in a\n225: temporary “authorization” hold. These holds are removed by your bank, typically within three to five\n226: days, and do not result in actual charges to your account.\n227: What payment methods does Oracle accept?\n228: We accept credit cards and debit cards that function like credit cards. We do not accept debit cards with\n229: a PIN or virtual, single-use, or prepaid cards.\n230: What is the advantage of moving to Pay As You Go accounts after the trial?\n231: You have access to customer support to open tickets and troubleshoot account issues. Pay As You Go\n232: accounts are subject to different capacity limits than Always Free accounts. As you move from\n233: development and testing to production scenarios, you may need to use resources outside of Always\n234: Free limits. You will have access to the latest portfolio of OCI services, such as artificial intelligence, and\n235: you only pay for what you use.\n236: How do I know how much I am going be charged for Pay As You Go services?\n237: You will only be charged for services that you use that exceeds Always Free. You can find information\n238: about costs in the Oracle Cloud Price List and the Oracle cloud cost estimator.CallSales\n239: +44 207 5626 823\n240: Complete list of local country numbers6/17/26, 5:58 PM Oracle Cloud Free Tier | Oracle United Kingdom\n241: https://www.oracle.com/uk/cloud/free/ 7/8\n242: --- PAGE 8 ---\n243: *Free Tier is generally available in regions where commercial Oracle Cloud Infrastructure service is available See\n244: the data regions page for detailed service availability (Exact regions available for Free Tier may differ during signup\n245: process). The US$300 cloud credit is available in select countries and valid for up to 30 days. Cloud credits\n246: consumption can be subject to discounted rates during the 30-day promotional period.\n247: ** Availability to Free Tier is subject to capacity limits. The capacity limits listed under each service are only\n248: estimates and reflect the maximum capacity you can get if you consume your entire credit on one service during\n249: the promotional period. The maximum capacity per service you get can be less if you consume multiple services.\n250: The list of services and capacity estimates are subject to change. Your credit balance is available to you in the\n251: Oracle Cloud Infrastructure Console.\n252: Terms of Use and Privacy Gender Pay Gap ReportModern Slavery Statement Ad Choices\n253: CareersSubscribe to emailsIntegrity Helpline Contact UsView all Oracle Cloud Free Tier FAQ\n254: © 2026 Oracle\n255: CallSales\n256: +44 207 5626 823\n257: Complete list of local country numbers6/17/26, 5:58 PM Oracle Cloud Free Tier | Oracle United Kingdom\n258: https://www.oracle.com/uk/cloud/free/ 8/8\n\n(End of file - total 258 lines)\n</content>",
