      "text": "Got everything I need. Here's the final OCI file map, grouped by purpose. No media attached — pure text tables so we don't blow the size budget again.\n\n---\n\n# 🟦 OCI / Oracle Cloud File Inventory — Final Report\n\n**Compiled:** 2026-06-22 · **Search scope:** Documents, Desktop, Downloads, LAMPForge_SDTP  \n**Critical finding:** A live **Oracle Cloud account exists** — see Section A.\n\n---\n\n## 🔴 SECTION A — ACCOUNT CREDENTIALS (FLAG IMMEDIATELY)\n\nThese three files contain real account details. **Do not share externally.**\n\n| File | Path | Modified | What's in it |\n|------|------|----------|--------------|\n| **Signup v1** | `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\Oracle Cloud Free Tier Signup.pdf` | 07/03/2026 | Account creation form screenshot |\n| **Signup v2** | `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\Oracle Cloud Free_Tier Signup.pdf` | 07/03/2026 | Verification & agreement page |\n| **Subscription email** | `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\Yahoo Mail - Oracle Cloud Services_ your subscription(s) has been updated.pdf` | 03/04/2026 | Subscription change email |\n\n### Account details extracted:\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **First Name** | Andie |\n| **Last Name** | Kobbie |\n| **Email (username)** | andiekobbietks@outlook.com |\n| **Legal Company** | LAMPForge Ltd |\n| **Cloud Account Name (tenancy namespace)** | andiekobbietks |\n| **Home Region** | UK South (London) |\n| **Country** | United Kingdom |\n| **Signup date** | 7 March 2026 (form), 8 March 2026 (verification) |\n| **Card on file** | ************0382, exp 2030/07 |\n| **Payment processor** | CyberSource |\n| **Account Type** | Individual (likely, given naming) |\n| **Status** | Free Tier account created |\n\n⚠️ **Note:** No tenancy OCID or user OCID is exposed in these PDFs — those are only visible after login. The `AKCLOUD-PRD-SDG-001.md` and `python_oci_backend_architecture.md` reference `ocid1.compartment.oc1..your-compartment` as a **placeholder**, meaning no real tenancy OCID was hard-coded anywhere I found.\n\n---\n\n## 📘 SECTION B — ORACLE OFFICIAL DOCUMENTATION\n\n| File | Path | Modified | Size |\n|------|------|----------|------|\n| Oracle UK Free Tier | `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\Oracle Cloud Free Tier _ Oracle United Kingdom.pdf` | 17/06/2026 | 1.7 MB |\n| Oracle UK FAQ | `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\FAQ on Oracle's Cloud Free Tier _ Oracle United Kingdom.pdf` | 17/06/2026 | 613 KB |\n\n**Key facts confirmed from Oracle UK docs (as of 17/06/2026):**\n\n- **Always Free services** include: Arm Ampere A1 Compute (1,500 OCPU hrs/month, 9,000 GB-hr/month), AMD Compute (2 VMs × 1/8 OCPU × 1 GB), Block/Object/Archive Storage, Flexible Load Balancer, VCN, Site-to-Site VPN, Autonomous Data Warehouse, Autonomous Transaction Processing, Autonomous JSON Database, APEX, Vault, Bastions, NoSQL (Phoenix only), Email Delivery, Monitoring/Notifications/Logging/APM.\n- **Trial:** US$300 credit, 30 days, then auto-converts to Always Free (or 30-day grace then deletion).\n- **One account per person.** Accounts idle ≥30 days may be suspended.\n- **No SLAs on Always Free**; community support only.\n- **Out-of-host-capacity errors** common for A1 — Oracle recommends trying different availability domains or waiting.\n\n---\n\n## 🏗️ SECTION C — THE REAL ARCHITECTURE: LAMPForge_SDTP `forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821`\n\nThis is the **active project** (last touched 25/03/2026 in `docs/`, 19/03/2026 in `RandD/`). The OCI Always Free ARM Ampere A1 + Autonomous Database 23ai stack is the canonical compute target.\n\n### C1. The Sovereign AI Stack — Core ADRs (PDF)\n\n| File | Path | Modified | What it contains |\n|------|------|----------|------------------|\n| **ADR-SOVEREIGN-AI-STACK.pdf** | `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\Opprah's Foundation Essentials\\ADR-SOVEREIGN-AI-STACK.md.pdf` | (newer than docs/) | **ADR-001 to ADR-009** — the master architectural decision record. This is the *source-of-truth* design. |\n\n**The 9 ADRs (all 2026-05-18, all \"Accepted\" except ADR-008 \"Proposed\"):**\n\n| ADR | Title | Key Decision |\n|-----|-------|--------------|\n| 001 | Oracle Autonomous Database 23ai as Converged Sovereign Platform | Single DB = relational + vector + CLOB + scheduler + ORDS. Uses 20 GB storage + 1 OCPU from Always Free. |\n| 002 | EmbeddingGemma 300M Loaded Natively via ONNX | `DBMS_VECTOR.LOAD_ONNX_MODEL` registers model; `UTL_TO_EMBEDDING` produces VECTOR(768, FLOAT32). No external embedding API. |\n| 003 | DBMS_VECTOR_CHAIN as the In-Database RAG Pipeline | 6-stage pipeline (chunk→embed→store→search→assemble→generate) all in PL/SQL. HNSW index, COSINE distance, top-5. |\n| 004 | DBMS_SCHEDULER as Autonomous Job Orchestration Kernel | `CREATE_CHAIN` SOVEREIGN_PIPELINE: L1 Harvester → L2 Refiner → L3 Librarian → L4 Judge. Nightly 02:00 UTC + event trigger on STAGING_ENTRIES. |\n| 005 | OCI Always Free ARM (Ampere A1) as Zero-Cost Compute Layer | 4 OCPUs, 24 GB RAM split: 16 GB Gemma4 + 6 GB Python middleware + 2 GB OS. LXD isolation, ARM NEON/ASIMD compile flags. |\n| 006 | Gemma 4 via Ollama as Sovereign Reasoning Engine | E4B at 4-bit GGUF, gemma-4-thinking template for auditable traces. OpenAI-compatible endpoint at `http://localhost:11434`. |\n| 007 | 8KB Compressed Working Memory Map as Passive Context | Vercel/Jude Gao research: 8KB pipe-delimited index = 100% pass rate vs 53% for RAG. Generated by `GENERATE_WORKING_MEMORY_MAP` PL/SQL fn. |\n| 008 | OML4Py Embedded Python for DFR-Gemma Projection Layer | (Proposed) PyTorch linear projector maps EmbeddingGemma 768-d → Gemma 4 latent token space. Trained on COHERENCE_LOG pairs. |\n| 009 | Coherence Indexing and Drift Detection | 3 signals: Golden Set accuracy (≥0.85 threshold), thought-token trend (+30% over baseline = drift), embedding centroid drift (>0.1 cosine). |\n\n### C2. The Oracle Linux + LXD Stack — ADRs 010–015 (PDF)\n\n| File | Path | Modified | What it contains |\n|------|------|----------|------------------|\n| **ORACLE-LINUX-LXD-SOLOPRENEUR.pdf** | `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\Opprah's Foundation Essentials\\ORACLE-LINUX-LXD-SOLOPRENEUR.md.pdf` | 18/05/2026 | **ADR-010 to ADR-015** — host OS, container layer, UI, profiles, snapshots, edge. |\n\n| ADR | Title | Key Decision |\n|-----|-------|--------------|\n| 010 | Oracle Linux 9 + UEK as Sovereign Host OS | UEK r7+ has cgroup v2, io_uring, virtiofs. UEK optimised for Ampere A1. Ubuntu rejected (glibc/UEK issues). |\n| 011 | LXD as Container and VM Orchestration Layer | 4 system containers: `gemma4` (16 GB / 3 OCPU), `openwebui` (4 GB / 0.5 OCPU), `oracle-client` (2 GB / 0.25 OCPU), `cloudflare-tunnel` (512 MB / 0.1 OCPU). All on `lxdbr0` bridge, only tunnel is externally exposed. |\n| 012 | LXD Web UI as Solopreneur's Operations Centre | Web UI on `https://<ip>:8443`, behind Cloudflare Tunnel split-tunnel or SSH. Browser-based terminal into any container. |\n| 013 | LXD Profiles as Terraform for the Solopreneur | 5 profiles: `base`, `inference`, `service`, `oracle-client`, `tunnel`. New client env = 3 commands. |\n| 014 | ZFS Snapshots as Insurance Policy | ZFS storage pool on OCI boot volume, ARC capped at 2 GB. Pre-pipeline auto-snapshot via `DBMS_SCHEDULER` shell step, retained 48 hr. |\n| 015 | Cloudflare Free Tier as Solopreneur's Edge Network | Cloudflare Tunnel (outbound-only) + WAF + DDoS + caching. Public IP never directly exposed (except SSH). |\n\n### C3. Companion Architecture Docs (Markdown, in `forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821`)\n\n| File | Path | Modified | Purpose |\n|------|------|----------|---------|\n| `RandD\\python_oci_backend_architecture.md` | `…\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\RandD\\` | 06/03/2026 | Original Python-on-OCI plan. Split: `sdtp-api` (2 OCPU/12 GB FastAPI) + `sdtp-db` (1/6 GB PostgreSQL) + `sdtp-cache` (1/6 GB Redis). The ADRs supersede this. |\n| `RandD\\terraform_iac_integration.md` | `…\\RandD\\` | 06/03/2026 | Vision for IaC in `.forge` pedagogy. **AWS-focused** (not OCI), but Terraform/OCI provider mentioned. |\n| `RandD\\one_click_bootstrapper_feasibility.md` | `…\\RandD\\` | (2026) | Honest assessment of bootstrap options. Recommended: portable Edge (extracted MSI to user-space) + Sovereign USB. |\n| `docs\\sovereign-ai-inference.md` | `…\\docs\\` | 16/03/2026 | Browser-native inference cascade: window.ai → ONNX Web → Foundry → cloud. Phi-4-mini as target. |\n| `docs\\SOVEREIGN_ARCHITECTURE_INSIGHTS.md` | `…\\docs\\` | 09/03/2026 | Zero-server communication via BroadcastChannel + OPFS hibernation + File System Access API for \"Sovereign Bridge.\" |\n| `docs\\SOVEREIGN_MCP_IDENTITY.md` | `…\\docs\\` | 16/03/2026 | \"Identity Membrane\" / ZKP Airbag wrapping MCP. Validates against MCP-I standard. |\n| `docs\\SOVEREIGN_SCENARIOS.md` | `…\\docs\\` | 09/03/2026 | 4 \"We Asked\" scenarios: air-gapped classroom, zero-budget school, no-install mandate, moderator audit (Mulberry32 PRNG). |\n| `internal\\docs-private\\sovereign_pde_architecture.md` | `…\\internal\\docs-private\\` | 07/03/2026 | 924-line master design doc — the PDE philosophy, GPO threat model, portable Edge supply chain, 4-tier deployment hierarchy, mesh/WebRTC multiplayer vision. |\n\n---\n\n## 📊 SECTION D — PROJECT PLANNING / PRDs\n\n| File | Path | Modified | What it is |\n|------|------|----------|-----------|\n| **AKCLOUD-PRD-SDG-001.md** | `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\AKCLOUD-PRD-SDG-001.md` | 14/06/2026 | **The main project spec.** By \"Andie Enning, compiled with Claude (Anthropic).\" Stack: OCI Always Free ARM + Cozystack/Talos on OCI Always Free + Odoo + LAMPForge + BigBlueButton. |\n| **AKCLOUD-PRD-SDG-001.pdf** | `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\AKCLOUD-PRD-SDG-001.pdf` | (similar) | PDF version of above. |\n| **sovereign_intelligence_business_plan.md / .pdf** | `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\sovereign_intelligence_business_plan.md.pdf` | (May 2026) | 429-line business plan — \"Sovereign Intelligence: A Business Plan for the Age of Digital Dignity.\" Three revenue streams: implementat